description: Sisters Kurako, Yuzu and Tama are Miko priestesses, entrusted with keeping an eye on the often volatile spirit world. But when you're a teenager like Yuzu, you want nothing more than to lead a normal life and deal with growing up and falling in love. Enter Tadahiro, the sisters' cousin, who has a mysterious connection to Yuzu's past--and a strained relationship with his other relatives. Alas, family drama may have to wait! The spirit world suddenly shifts out of balance, unleashing demons into our world who have set their sights on Tadahiro...
name: Vol. 1

description: Trouble seems to follow Tadahiro everywhere he goes. When the school is inundated with rampaging apparitions, a student taskforce is formed to combat the evil spirits. Tadahiro narrowly averts disaster when an unexpected new friend rescues him during one of the attacks... But this surprising, newfound ally may have less than noble intentions in mind for Yuzu's young cousin!
name: Vol. 2

description: As the Culture Festival approaches, the Priestess Committee find itself hard-pressed to think of a suitable contribution. But this may be the least of Yuzus headaches, as she suffers relentless torment from both the evil Ayatachi and her class nemesis, Kusugi. And as the attacks grow more frequent and viscous, Tadahiro feels increasingly guilty about the danger hes putting Yuzu in...never knowing that the worst is yet to come!
name: Vol. 3

description: Ayatachi and Kukuri plan to take Yuzu from the shrine once and for all. Tadahiro seems to be the only one to notice Kukuris politeness is not truly sincere. He must convince Yuzu to be careful around Kukuri, but it is hard to convince someone when they don't even believe in you. Tadahiro must protect Yuzu at all costs, even if it means losing his life.
name: Vol. 4

description:
Megan was a young photography student attending Santa Monica Community College. She began having very real and troubling dreams the night she saw a suicidal young man named AJ Crandall walk fully clothed into the ocean and vanish in the fog. Since then, Megan's curious therapist, Petier Troia, seemed to provide little comfort from Megan's dreams, dreams where she visited with the deceased AJ in a tranquil summer-set meadow. Events took a turn for the bizarre during one troubled sleep in which Megan found herself enlisted as a living ShutterBox exchange student at Merridiah University of Spiritual Education (or M.U.S.E.). She returned to Merridiah University on December 25th to begin her education as a living Muse. When she once again met the brothers AJ and Dane, she also learned that her therapist, Petier Troia, was in actuality Headmaster Petier Troia, probably the most important Muse in all of Merridiah.

With help from the ghost who lives inside her camera, the secrets behind the great gothic castle that is Merridiah University began to unravel for Megan the night she peered through the shutter of her camera lens, opening a mystery inside a mystery, inside a mystery, inside a mystery...
name: Orientation

description: Megan awakens from a dream to find that she is in the afterlife as a full time exchange student. A spirit inhabiting Megan's camera tells her that her mother is being tormented on earth by an evil banshee who took her place on Earth. With the help of her possessed camera, Megan and her friends Thomas and AJ struggle to banish the banshee from her mother's life!
name: First School Quarter

description: Drowning in a Sea of Lies Unless Megan can capture the terrible Banshee she accidentally unleashed, her time at Merridiah University--and her life--will come to a very sad, sudden end! While on her life-and-death quest, Megan discovers an eternal entity once thought lost within Merridiah University's heart. Some secrets may be better left undisclosed, however--including the shocking revelations about a past Megan does not recall with a man she cannot stand!
name: Entry Exam

description: To be once more a child for one bright summer's day... Now that Megan has merged with the goddess Laahli, Megan discovers that she can teleport to any place within Merridiah she desires. As a result of this newfound power, she and Adrien have spent many days alone together, thousands of miles away from Merridiah University. Yet the many creatures of Merridiah are terrified at the idea of Megan's divine union with Laahli--after a meeting of Merridiah's leaders, Damien hatches a plan to imprison Megan within university grounds...
name: The Angel of Childhood's End

description: Its just one thing after another for Rakan and co. Strange houses with no walls, stone creatures, black beasts, and yet another assassin sent to finish off the Sanome Prince once and for all...and while Rakan heads toward his confrontation with the Imperial Prince above ground, below his personal body guards are also making progress. But in the end, is Rakan just promising the impossible? Can Narushige keep everyone together? And why cant Chigusa ever keep his shirt on?!
name: Stone Wolf

description: Rakan and co. continue their journey towards the Imperial Capital, but new obstacles continue to get in their way. Enormous snakes begin to emerge from the ground, wreaking havoc before disintegrating into streams of water--could this be the next part of the Ayame Prince's prophesy? And Narushige recalls his painful past as his younger sister learns just what it means that she has become the next "Sacrificial Child."
name: After Death

description: Despite losing the Wasps and Chameleons, Rasputin still has the upper hand against the Skull Man. He has captured both Detective Hioka and Maria, and taken them to his undersea command base. There Rasputin tries to use his own psychic powers to mutate Hioka into one of his warrior-slaves, and to force Maria to reveal the Skull Man's secrets. Things go awry when Hioka proves to be so morally resolute that he can withstand Rasputin's dominance, and Maria's new psychic link to the Skull Man enables her to transform into Skull Maria to fight back against Rasputin. But this advantage suddenly becomes a deadly weakness when the Skull Man, in Toyko, is attacked by yet another of the organization's freakish killers, the Vulture Man.
name: Vol. 6

description: Rasputin's as-of-yet-unseen boss warns the Syndicate leader that if he fails to execute the Skull Man once and for all, he himself will be eliminated. With nothing else to lose, Rasputin issues a challenge to the Skull Man, a call for all out war between them. However, infighting in Rasputin's ranks severely weaken his team and the Skull Man returns to his secluded base to meet with Maya and Garo and unveil his feat of genetic engineering, Tobioka. But Garo may hold a secret that will unveil important details of a guarded past.
name: Vol. 7

description: Tomo, a sweet high school girl, loves living near the beach. However, after her parents got divorced, her frequent beach visits became no more. Until one day, after getting harassed on her way to school, Tomo is rescued by a selfless, very attractive stranger who somehow reminds her of the ocean. As the stranger leaves, he drops his keys, and Tomo realizes the keyring has the same stone as one given to her by a long lost friend from her childhood. Could he be the same person? Tomo believes the sea can bestow treasures on people, and she may be about to be proven right in ways she didnt imagine!
name: Vol. 1

description:
Ryosuke Kinuta is a struggling young actor with a mounting problem--his unpaid debts to loan sharks have caught up with him, so they cut a deal, offering him a different type of role. Ryosuke will work as their "carrier," but unfortunately, this isn't the big break he has been hoping for. He has to smuggle the bodies of murdered victims, making sure they're never to be seen again...or he'll never be seen again!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: The Transporter
  • Chapter 2: Spine and Gut
  • Chapter 3: Back of a Truck
  • Chapter 4: Preparation
name: Vol. 1

description: Love! Destruction! Space pirates! Deep dark secrets! And really, really big robots! The Warmongers are the most feared force in the galaxy. And rightfully so. They are gigantic and imposing, and terror is always reflected in their dark, metallic hide. The Warmongers are masters of grand design, hell-bent on complete domination through force and nefarious technologies. And their latest creation is their most wicked weapon yet: The Ghost of Destruction! Humanoid in appearance, The Ghost looks like a pale boy...until he unleashes his deadly powers! A whirlwind of annihilation, The Ghost is capable of leveling entire planets! And one by one, planets are crumbling under the Warmongers' steely boots... Except the planet Hub, an icy world, with a single area called Refuse City as its only oasis. Hub is a backwoods planet, far from the reach of the brutal warmongers. If you want to hide, if you want to remain off the radar, if you want to start a new life without being asked questions, Hub is the place for you. Snow, a young man with a scarred face, arrives on Hub to escape his mysterious past... Although he's out from the watchful eye of the Warmongers, Hub isn't exactly safe. Most of the inhabitants of Hub hide a shady past, and Snow soon realizes that Hub is controlled by S.S.C.A.B. (The Space Syndicate of Criminals, Assassins and Bandits). Snow soon forges an alliance with a local vigilante gang called "The Crows." A relationship between Snow and the spunky leader of The Crows, Katarina, quickly forms, and it is this bond that will give Snow the strength to survive the challenges ahead.
name: Vol. 1
Planet Man-Azon, and Fun with Head-Sucking Alens

description: Nightmares & Fairy Tales is a continuing series filled with dark fairy tales and horror stories , all narrated by Annabelle, a disturbingly creepy-cute little doll. Issue one focuses on Morgan who has just recently acquired Annabelle along with the troubles of her deranged friend Dominique. Morgan finds herself wrapped up in a series of horrible events, it seems that all her friends are turning up dead and poor Morgan is afraid that she may be responsible for the murders. Join Annabelle (our narrator) in the first of many spooky stories to come.
name: The Story of Morgan & Dominique Pt. 1

description: Poor little Morgan laying on the bathroom floor in a pool of blood, an understandably freaked out Morgan embarks on a search for some answers as to why her friends are being murdered. Unfortunately, she goes a little crazy when all the evidence points in her direction. Join the little doll named Annabelle (our narrator) for the horrifying conclusion of the first story in this ongoing series from the writer of GloomCookie.
name: The Story of Morgan & Dominique Pt. 2

description: Our doll narrator Annabelle finds herself back in New Orleans where Dominique's story began. This issue focuses on Dominique, and how she became the "monster" she is today. Having been sent to an ominous nunnery in New Orleans, Dominique finds herself wrapped in terrifying nightmares and unspeakable horrors. Learn Dominique's tale as Annabelle revisits the past in this disturbing story of wicked nuns and monsters in the attic.
name: The Haunted Nunnery: Dominique's Story

description: "The Enchanted Mirror." Sitting in the grave yard where Dominique left her, Annabelle recounts the story of Snow White... but not quite the way you remember it. With the help of an enchanted mirror, an evil and ugly queen takes the heart of her step-daughter in hopes of regaining her beauty. But Snow does not die. She wants her heart back - and she's willing to do anything to get it! Please join us for the horrifying fourth installment in this continuing series.
name: The Enchanted Mirror: Snow's Story

description: There is a secret lurking in the closets, between the walls and under the floor of Gwen?s new house. Join Annabelle in this spooky installment of this continuing series, as Gwen struggles with moving to a new home and finding that sometimes it's your parents that are the 'real' monsters? Rather than that thing making that thumping noise under the stairs.
name: Moving Day: Gwen's Story

description:
Annabelle recalls sitting in the doll shop, and recounts the story of the first woman who took her home in the modern world. A woman who tragically falls in love with a man who can not marry her...after all he isn't a man at all... he is a ghost.

Note: This issue is cover dated as April 2004, while the following issue is dated March 2004. It is likely that SLG changed their dating scheme between the two issues, resulting in this error.
name: The Ghost and the Doll Shop - Paige's Story

description: Alone in the forest, on her way to her Grandmother's house, a young girl comes across an enchanting and mysterious man who may very well be a werewolf! Join Annabelle as she recounts the story of Little Red Riding Hood...but with a spooky and surprising twist!
name: Luna's Story: Little Red Riding Hood

description: Annabelle, Gwen, and her new friend Bunny find themselves in a haunted house full of mirrors that trap the souls of dead children... Hopefully Annabelle will be able to save them
name: Gwen & the Magical Tree

description: A late-1940's thriller, presented in glorious black-and-white! A frightening tale of murder, romance and ghostly visits from the beyond, as told by a little doll named Annabelle.
name: A Woman Possessed!: Part One

description: The Chilling conclusion of "A Woman Possessed!" A late 1940's thriller in glorious black and white! Catherine is being haunted by a woman who was mysteriously murdered and the ghost is causing her to loose her mind, casting suspicion on Catherine.
name: A Woman Possessed!: Part Two

description:
1140 Rue Royale - Part One of Six

In Antebellum New Orleans, Delphine Lalaurie inflicted unspeakable acts upon her slaves in the house at 1140 Rue Royale. now their tortured souls are seeking revenge on the house's new occupants, an elderly woman named Victorian and her young niece Rebecca.
name: 1140 Rue Royale - Part One of Six

description: Victoria seeks the help of the church when things start to get frightfully dangerous in this continuing story about an older woman and her young niece who move into a house that is haunted by the vengeful victims of horrific crimes.
name: 1140 Rue Royale - Part Two of Six

description: "1140 Rue Royale" continues... Victoria & Rebecca are being tormented by malicious spirits, the victims of horrific crimes that were inflicted by the house's previous owner, Madame Lalaurie. Desperate for help, Victoria appeals to the sisters at the nunnery for assistance, putting all of their lives in grave danger.
name: 1140 Rue Royale - Part Three of Six

description: Victoria fears Rebecca has either become possessed or is being coerced by their ghostly tormentors, and has Rebecca committed and put under the care of the nuns at The Ursuline Convent, putting all of their lives in grave danger.
name: 1140 Rue Royale - Part Four of Six

description:
Victoria and Rebecca struggle to survive in this continuing story about an older woman and her young niece who move into a house that is haunted by the vengeful victims of horrific crimes that were inflicted by the house's previous owner, Madame Lalaurie.

Note: Annabelle, the series' narrator and only constant character, does not appear in this issue in any capacity.
name: 1140 Rue Royale - Part Five of Six

description:
In this issue, the tortured souls of Madame Lalaurie's victims want revenge, placing Rebecca and Victoria in a fight for their lives!

Notes: This issue's cover date is February 2006 while the preceding issue's date was July 2006. It is likely that this issue had it's actual in-store date printed on the cover while the previous issue had an advance date on it, as comics often do.

Annabelle, the series' narrator and only constant character, does not appear in this issue in any capacity.
name: 1140 Rue Royale - Part Six of Six

description: 'Sleeping Beauty's Story' - Part 1 of 2! Gwen and Aunt Bea take a trip to San Francisco where they encounter the spirit of a lovely young woman wandering the Sutro Bath ruins in this modern and breathtaking adaptation of Sleeping Beauty.
name: Harmony: Sleeping Beauty's Story, Part One of Two

description: This issue continues the 'Sleeping Beauty' story from the previous issue, and Camilla d'Errico once again brings her vibrant visual styling to this series!
name: Harmony: Sleeping Beauty's Story, Part Two of Two

description: Floyd Farlan livesin a totaitarian "future" world where overpopulation and technology have ruined society. A sly totalitarian state rules everything, inducing to their citizens to desire and do anything it want. In this decadent world, everyone is in rebellion to the government, except Floyd Farland. This makes him very suspicious and dangerous to the government's eyes.Because of this, Floyd is taken as an undergroud leader and captured, tortured, brainwashed, rescued, hailed as savior, captured again, nearly killed and mind-wiped.
name: Floyd Farland: Citizen of the Future

volume.name: Floyd Farland: Citizen of the Future

description: A beautiful mermaid is ensnared by a sideshow charlatan and put on display - bringing her captor quite a bit of revenue - until a string of mysterious deaths casts a shadow on the traveling carnival. Inspired by the H.P. Lovecraft novella 'Shadow over Innsmouth'
name: Song of the Siren, Part One of Three

description: The story of a beautiful mermaid ensnared by Lucas, a sideshow charlatan and put on display in his traveling carnival is inspired by H.P. Lovecraft's 'Shadow over Innsmouth.' The carnival is forced to move to another town after two of Mea's girls are murdered by religious zealots. Meanwhile, the horrible tale behind the mermaid's capture and the grizzly consequences to Lucas are revealed.
name: Song of the Siren, Part Two of Three

description: Icaro is a young man blessed with the fantastic ability of flight. But his home - a secret laboratory complex - is in reality a high-tech prison and Icaro is the guinea it was created to study. But in the staff of the laboratory is one person who rebels at the sinisters plan for Icaro. Yukiko is a young woman who is willing to risk her life to free the boy who has never known freedom.
name: Icaro

description: The gruesome and horrifying conclusion to 'Song of the Siren,' the story of a beautiful mermaid ensnared by Lucas, an abusive sideshow charlatan and put on display in his traveling carnival. The carnival is in panic when the mermaid escapes with intent to kill Lucas. Meanwhile, learn the horrible tale behind the mermaid's capture and the grizzly consequences Lucas suffered for his foul deeds. An exquisitely frightening and disturbing tale written by Serena Valentino, inspired by H.P. Lovecraft's 'Shadow over Innsmouth,' and beautifully illustrated by Camilla d'Errico.
name: Song of the Siren, Part Three of Three
